{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1943 |Team=Notre Dame Fighting Irish |Image= |ImageSize=150 px |Conference=Independent |Division= |ShortConference= |APRank=1 |Record=9-1 |ConfRecord= |HeadCoach=[[Frank Leahy]] |OffCoach=[[T formation|T-Formation]] |DefCoach= |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Notre Dame Stadium]] (c. 59,075, grass) |Champion=National Champions }} The '''1943 Notre Dame Fighting Irish football team''' represented the [[University of Notre Dame]] during the [[1943 college football season]]. The Irish, coached by [[Frank Leahy]], ended the season with 9 wins and 1 loss, winning the [[NCAA Division I-A national football championship|national championship]].<ref name="2007 ND Guide History">{{cite web |url=http://und.cstv.com/auto_pdf/p_hotos/s_chools/nd/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/07fbguidehistory |title = 2007 Notre Dame Media Guide: History and Records (pages 131-175) | publisher= und.cstv.com | accessdate=2009-01-01}}</ref> The 1943 team became the fourth Irish team to win the national title and the first for Frank Leahy. Led by Notre Dame's first [[Heisman Trophy]] winner, [[Angelo Bertelli]], Notre Dame beat seven teams ranked in the top 13 and played seven of its ten games on the road.<ref name="2007 ND Guide Supplement" >{{cite web |url= http://www.cstv.com/auto_pdf/p_hotos/s_chools/nd/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/Football-Supplement-07 |title = 2007 Notre Dame Media Guide: 2007 Supplement (page 163) | publisher= und.cstv.com | accessdate=2008-12-31}}</ref> Despite a season ending loss to Great Lakes, Notre Dame was awarded its first national title by the [[Associated Press]].<ref name="FBS Past National Champions">{{cite web |url=http://www.ncaa.org/champadmin/ia_football_past_champs.html |title = Past Division I Football Bowl Subdivision (Division I FBS) National Champions (formerly called Division I-A) | publisher= ncaa.org | accessdate=2009-01-01|archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20080509084329/http://www.ncaa.org/champadmin/ia_football_past_champs.html |archivedate = May 09, 2008|deadurl=yes}} </ref>
